Nov 5, 2021:
------------

* vars and stringstores
    * keys can obviously be names (as opposed to filenames)
    * vals aren't obviously names or filenames
    * currently, in hexgame, vars_t is modified (exclusively?) via valexpr_t
        * string values are therefore stored as "literals" owned by valexprs
        * src/hexgame_state.c: state_effect_apply:
            case STATE_EFFECT_TYPE_{INC,DEC,SET}:
                * uses valexpr_set on &effect->u.set.var_expr to get a val_t* for the "lvalue"
                * uses valexpr_get on &effect->u.set.val_expr to get a val_t* for the "rvalue"
                * {INC,DEC} do val_get_int on the rvalue, then val_set_int on the lvalue
                * SET does val_copy from the rvalue to the lvalue
                    * !!! val_copy for VAL_TYPE_STR uses strdup!..
                        * so this is what we might like to "fix"...
                        * currently, vals are only copied around, but we might eventually
                          want to add support for concat, etc
                          So, any stringstore stuff we implement should work with that.
                          If we had VAL_TYPE_NAME and VAL_TYPE_FILENAME, that could work.
                          But that's... obviously ganky.
                          Instead, it probably makes most sense to have one stringstore
                          used by all vars_t and valexpr_t in hexgame.
                          According to: nano $(ack -l "  vars_t" src/*.h)
                          ...the places we use vars_t in hexgame are:

                            hexmap_recording_t:
                                vars
                                bodyvars
                            hexcollmap_part_t:
                                vars
                                bodyvars
                            body_t:
                                vars
                            actor_t:
                                vars
                            hexgame_t:
                                vars
                            hexmap_t:
                                vars

                        * Ok, I think this is what makes sense:
                            * Have one stringstore for vars (vars_store)
                            * It's used for all keys
                                * Would need to add support for var_t not owning its keys!
                            * It's used for all parsed vals
                                * With VAL_TYPE_STR
                            * If we add dynamically-generated vals (e.g. "concat" etc),
                              maybe don't use the stringstore?..
                                * So, use VAL_TYPE_STR with an owned string (val->s)?..
                                * !!! I'm not sure about this. Anyway, it doesn't really
                                  matter right now.

* recording_t should have vars, so e.g. data/recs/coin_crouch.fus should have state "init" and
  vars: "crouch": T, whereas currently it has state "crouch".


