Dec 11, 2021:
-------------

src/hexgame_savelocation.[ch]:

    Currently hexgame_savelocation_{save,load} is saving/loading the following things:
        * The passed hexgame_savelocation_t *savelocation
        * The passed hexgame_t *game's vars, maps, and map->vars for each map
    ...that's not quite right, we need to save e.g. body's vars as well.
    And it's a hack that we're pretending that this is a single data structure,
    when it's actually treating THE ENTIRE GAME AND ITS MAPS as part of the data. O_o

    The actual data structure (as defined in hexgame_savelocation.h) is:

        typedef struct hexgame_savelocation {
            hexgame_location_t loc;
            const char *map_filename;
            const char *stateset_filename;
            const char *state_name;
        } hexgame_savelocation_t;

    We use this structure in the following places:

        hexmap_door.u.location /* type == HEXMAP_DOOR_TYPE_RESPAWN or HEXMAP_DOOR_TYPE_NEW_GAME */
        player.respawn_location
        player.safe_location
        player_use_savepoint -> hexgame_savelocation_save
        player_reload -> hexgame_savelocation_load

    ...ok I think the deal is:

        * There are multiple kinds of "saving" going on
        * player.respawn_location and player.safe_location shouldn't have anything to do with vars, maps, etc
        * Touching a savepoint should update player.respawn_location *AND* save the game's state
        * The game's state includes:
            * Players (all of them?.. or just the "main" player, "player 1"?..)
                * player->respawn_location
                * player->body.vars
            * game->vars
            * game->maps
                * map->vars

...also, when all of this is done,

    !!! WE NEED TO MAKE SURE THAT SAVING & RELOADING DOESN'T RESULT IN YOU BEING STUCK !!!

...for instance, if you carry a mini_eye, then shoot it, and save while it's in the air,
and then reload the game, we need to make sure the mini_eye isn't permanently gone.

    ...HOWEVER, AN ALTERNATE APPROACH IS:

        * Don't save body->vars, just map->vars
        * So if you are carrying something, the relevant mapvars should be marked nosave
        * !!! THIS IS DE FACTO WHAT WE HAVE STARTED DOING !!!


